#Django REST API Authentication Guide

This repository serves as a structured learning resource for understanding Django REST Framework (DRF) and implementing REST API authentication, including JSON Web Token (JWT) authentication.

## 1. Introduction to Django REST Framework (DRF)

Django REST Framework (DRF) is a powerful and flexible toolkit for building Web APIs in Django. It provides features like:

- Serialization (converting Django models to JSON and vice versa)
- Authentication and permissions
- Class-based views and viewsets
- Browsable API for quick testing and debugging

### Why Use DRF?

- Clean separation of backend logic and API interface
- Easily connects with frontend frameworks like React, Vue, etc.
- Support for various authentication schemes (Token, Session, JWT)
- Highly customizable and scalable

